<HEADLINE> Thai Cabinet Approves Plan on Containing Water Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The Thai cabinet on Tuesday
approved a plan to curb water pollution as part of a mounting
campaign to protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
The plan, submitted by the Transport and Communications
Ministry, will be submitted to parliament for approval, a
government press release said.
</P>
<P>
The plan outlines the following steps for the protection of
water resources:
</P>
<P>
-- Specify the international regulation on the control and
protection of oil waste and dangerous substances which are
released from ships and other water transports in order to
preserve and protect marine natural resources and environment;
</P>
<P>
-- Create the international cooperation in protecting and
resolving pollution from marine transport under the International
Maritime Organization;
</P>
<P>
-- Create academic cooperation between member countries in
order to develop human resources and modernize technology of
pollution protection methods and equipment, and
</P>
<P>
-- Specify the regulation of toxic disposal management in the
sea such as oil, poisonous and toxic substances which are
contained in goods containers and other waste. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
