<HEADLINE> Britain FM to Visit Lockerbie Trial Site in Holland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 12 (Xinhua) - British Foreign Secretary Robin
Cook will travel to the Netherlands on Wednesday and visit Camp
Zeist, the site chosen for the Lockerbie trial.
</P>
<P>
Cook will also visit the International Criminal Tribunal for
the former Yugoslavia at the Hague, and he will talk with Dutch
Foreign Minister Josias van Aartsen, a British official said.
</P>
<P>
The two Libyans accused of masterminding the bombing of an
American airliner over Lockerbie, Scotland, in December 1988, and
killing all 259 people on board, and 11 others on the ground, are
expected to be tried at Camp Zeist. 
</P>
