<HEADLINE> EU Survey Shows Improvement in Economic Sentiment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the survey, consumer confidence maintained its
improving trend both in the EU and euro zone. The main reason for
this improvement lies in the sustained optimistic evaluation of
the present general economic situation and consumers showing a
positive attitude towards major purchases.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, industry managers expressed a more
optimistic view in their production expectations compared to that
of November. In the 15 EU countries, all assessments concerning
the level of order books stabilized, though the prevailing view
on their export books was more pessimistic.
</P>
<P>
Overall, the EU industrial confidence indicator improved in
December, albeit below its long-term average, the survey said.
</P>
</TEXT>
