<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-12 15:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 10 Arrested in Iran Related to Political Murders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Ten Iranian Intelligence agents
have been arrested so far in connection with the murders of five
liberals in the country.
</P>
<P>
A special committee in charge of investigating the murder cases
said in a report that a group of others are currently under
surveillance, according to the Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA)
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
There is more concrete information on the serial killings
"which cannot be divulged, because such disclosure would hurt the
still pending investigations," the committee said.
</P>
<P>
The committee was formed under the order of President Mohammad
Khatami, a moderate cleric, after the deaths of a prominent
opposition leader and his wife.
</P>
<P>
Dariush Foruhar and his wife were stabbed to death at home, and
the other three were dissident writers who were found murdered in
the suburbs of the capital city late last year.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Intelligence Ministry, under the control of the
conservatives, admitted that some of its agents were involved in
the killings.
</P>
<P>
This was a big blow to the conservatives, who have been engaged
in a bitter power struggle with the moderates, led by the
president.
</P>
<P>
However, the majority of the Iranian leadership, including the
paramount leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, pointed finger at foreign
enemies. The conservatives also hit back, accusing Khatami's
supporters of committing the crimes.
</P>
<P>
With most of the organs of the state power under their sway,
the conservatives lashed out at their rivals for trying to take
over the Intelligence Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The moderate factions have called for the resignation of
Intelligence Minister Qorbanali Dorri Najafabadi and an open trial
on the case.
</P>
<P>
The special investigation committee warned against factional
fighting over the killings and called on them to refrain from
creating tensions surrounding the issue.
</P>
<P>
Disruptions and ballyhoo by any party indicate that it does not
favor disclosure of the truth about the murders, and it will lose
through such revelations, the committee said.
</P>
<P>
The committee assured the public that it would continue the
investigations to the conclusion regardless of any tensions
intentionally created by some parties.
</P>
<P>
The investigations have identified "the architects and
executors of the operational phase," it said, and further
investigation to identify "the outside links and the principal
figures behind the murders" are underway. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
