<HEADLINE> Businessmen Fail to Renew Licenses in Addis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 12 (xinhua) -- Addis Ababa City Trade,
Industry and Tourism Bureau Tuesday said that 25 percent of the
businessmen operating in the capital have failed to comply with
the law which requires them to renew their licenses.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency quoted bureau head Gebre-Kidan
Wolde-Simon as saying that the bureau has filed suits against
12,460 businessmen who allegedly failed to renew their licenses in
this Ethiopian year.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen must renew their licenses every year in accordance
with the law. The current Ethiopian year started on September 11,
1998 and more than 50,000 business institutions are reportedly
registered in the capital.
</P>
<P>
Gebre-Kidan urged businessmen to renew their licenses before
they take legal measures.
</P>
<P>
He said the new proclamation stipulates that a business firm
which fails to renew its license on time will be obliged to stop
activities and has to wait for a year to regain their license.
</P>
