<HEADLINE> 82 Foreign Illegal Immigrants Detained in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Turkish gendarme forces Tuesday
detained 82 foreigners, who want to go to Greece illegally, in
western Turkey on Tuesday, the semi-official Anatolia News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the gendarme forces took three persons,
including one Pakistani and two Turks, into custody on charges of
helping the immigrants to go to Greece illegally in Izmir
province.
</P>
<P>
After the three arrested persons confessed that they hid the
foreigners in a forest in Doganbey of Izmir province, the Turkish
gendarme forces detained 42 Pakistani immigrants and 40
Bangladeshi immigrants.
</P>
<P>
Turkish officials said that the three persons who helped the
foreigners go to Greece illegally, had a deal with the immigrants
to take them to Athens with a private yatch, which would come from
Greece, for 2,500 U.S. dollars for one person.
</P>
<P>
The detained illegal immigrants will be deported from Turkey,
said the officials. 
</P>
