<HEADLINE> IMF Team to Recommend Release of Funds to Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- An International Monetary Fund
(IMF) team in Zimbabwe said Tuesday it will recommend that the the
53-million-U.S.- Dollar stand-by facility money to be disbursed to
Zimbabwe be released soon.
</P>
<P>
IMF Africa Director Goodall Gondwe said at a news conference in
Harare that the team was satisfied with discussions held with
various government ministries, but a final decision would be made
in Washington D.C.
</P>
<P>
The recommendation to be made to the board of the IMF early
March, will set in motion a process stalled for many months by
Zimbabwe's land reform policy, expenses being incurred in the
Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) war and the privatization of
Hwange Thermal Power Station.
</P>
<P>
Zimbabwe needs the crucial stand-by facility for balance of
payments support and general stabilization of the macro-economy.
