<HEADLINE> Meeting on Palestinian Refugees to be Held in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- An international meeting on the
Palestinian refugees is scheduled be held in Egypt on January 25,
Palestinian diplomatic sources here said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The International Coordination Committee on the Palestinian
Refugees and the Displaced will hold two-day meetings in the Sinai
resort of Sharm el-Sheikh on social programs and training courses
carried out in the host countries of the refugees, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the host countries, including Egypt, Jordan,
Lebanon, Syria, Canada, Italy, Spain and Japan, will take part in
the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will also deal with issues pertaining to ways of
solving problems facing the Palestinian refugees and guaranteeing
their return to home, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Israel's occupation of Palestine through four Middle East wars
with Arab countries in the past half a century has reduced
millions of Palestinians to refugees.
</P>
<P>
The International Coordination Committee for the Palestinian
Refugees and the Displace was formed in 1994 within the framework
of the multilateral Middle East peace negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The committee froze its activities after holding three meetings
due to the intransigent policies towards the peace process taken by
Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu since he assumed power
in 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
