recent days due to the postponement of an Arab foreign ministers
meeting on the Iraqi issue from December 30 to January 24.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has accused Egypt of maneuvering the postponement for
Kuwait and Saudi Arabia, which have not forgiven Saddam for Iraq's
invasion of Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
Egypt, in return, criticized the Iraqi leadership for adopting
unwise policies, resulting in one crisis after another in the
country and the sufferings of the Iraqi people due to the
crippling international economic sanctions triggered by its
invasion of Kuwait. 
