<HEADLINE> Heavy Snowfall Comes Down on Paris, Northern France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The first snowfall this winter
came down Tuesday afternoon on Paris and northern France, causing
widespread traffic jams in the Paris region and a rush hour chaos
of public transport.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 200 kilometers of traffic jams were reported late
Tuesday afternoon in the Ile-de-France comprising Paris and its
surrounding areas, as snow of three to four centimeters covered
the roads and fields in less than two hours.
</P>
<P>
Public bus transport was disrupted by the snowfall in the
region, while trains were overcrowded with passengers.
</P>
<P>
No major accidents have been reported so far, although some
losses of materials caused by the snowfall took place on the
roads.
</P>
<P>
The authorities are mobilizing the personnel of the Directions
Departmentales de l'Equipement, which is in charge of road
maintenance, for the whole night, which is expecting more
snowfalls.
</P>
<P>
In the prefecture of Seine-Maritime north of Paris, the
government has ordered a suspension of transporting schoolchildren
on school buses because of slippery roads.
</P>
<P>
In the northern region of Nord-Pas-de-Calais, snowfalls were
particularly heavy in the coastal areas as well as the cities of
Lille and Arras.
</P>
<P>
In the southeastern region of Rhone-Alpes, the authorities are
working hard to re-establish electricity for thousands of
households living in mountainous villages, after snowfalls cut
electricity supplies from Sunday to Monday.
</P>
<P>
The weather broadcast service Meteo-France said snow will fall
on the Massif Central and Champagne in central France, Lorraine
and Alsace in the east and Rhone-Alpes Tuesday night till
Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
