<HEADLINE> Guo Wins Men's Gold, Challenger Li Stumbles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, Jilin Province, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Guo
Zhengxin, Olympic eighth-place finisher, snatched the figure
skating men's singles gold in China's Winter Games Wednesday
night, while his challenger Li Chengjiang stumbled four times and
dropped to seventh.
</P>
<P>
Li, who beat Guo to second and led to the free skating after
Monday's short program, stumbled on his program-opening quad loop
and crashed every time on the following quad-triple attempts,
almost giving up after the third and the hardest fall.
</P>
<P>
He carried on his program with the half-packed Five Rings
Stadium tapping on his quick-stepping tempo, finishing just
seventh.
</P>
<P>
Guo, who skated to a lackluster free skating program with some
half-finished jumps, escaped with a gold medal which he thought a
gift from his national teammate.
</P>
<P>
"He (Li) didn't finished his training this morning," Guo said.
"I guess he might be injured."
</P>
<P>
"Li strained his back in Monday's short program," his coach
Gao Haijun confirmed with tears in eyes. "We knew we could lose
the best chance to fulfil our hope."
</P>
<P>
Li Yunfei and Li Xia took the second and third places
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions Zhang Weina and Cao Xianming skated to a
spectacular dance to win the ice dancing on Wednesday's
afternoon, followed by Wang Rui and Zhangwei on second. Qi Lina
and Gao Hao from Qiqihar finished third.
</P>
<P>
In the women's singles, which lost Olympic bronze medalist
Chen Lun, Lu Meijia took the gold with the least-flawed
performance while no competitors skated off the ring without
tumbles. 
