<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Outlines This Year's Water Control Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Wen Jiabao
presented the major principles and tasks of water-control
projects this year at a national conference here today.
</P>
<P>
He asked all parts of the country to implement major river
control plans and to repair damaged water control works, as
detailed by the State Council after last summer's devastating
floods.
</P>
<P>
This year's 10 major principles, he said, are needed for a
country that has been hit by floods and drought and an equal
effort is needed to improve the country's ability to fight both.
</P>
<P>
There will be an overall plan for the development and
protection of water resources and prevention of soil erosion, he
said. Key water control projects will need a scientific study and
will be subject to comparisons and project supervision for the
whole process of construction. Project safety should be above
all, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Because China has a serious water problem, conservation
methods like spray and drip irrigation will be used in all parts
of the country. And, to ensure development, China will stop the
felling of natural forests on the upper reaches of major rivers
and will open up new water resources, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
