<HEADLINE> Italy Sets Up Hotline for Euro Questions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A special free telephone hotline
has been activated in Italy recently to answer questions and
provide information about the newly-launched single currency euro.
</P>
<P>
The green number of hotline, which is 167-112002, should be
very easy to remember because the formal date of circulating euro
is January 1, 2002.
</P>
<P>
The Italian Treasury Ministry has set up the call center,
which will be staffed by 50 operators, and the call center will
answer questions and refer callers to other agencies for further
information.
</P>
<P>
The service, which is free for callers, is part of a broader
effort by Italian government and the European Union to tell
citizens about the single currency. 
</P>
</TEXT>
