<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 42.76 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Wednesday closed at 3310.46 as
against last close of 3353.22, netting a fall of 42.76 points.
</P>
<P>
The national index dipped by 21.05 points to 1475.13 from the
previous close of 1496.18.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and the U.S. dollar index were quoted substantially
down at 341.38 and 133.73 compared with the previous close of
344.90 and 135.11 respectively.
</P>
<P>
After initial signs of a recovery, equities reacted sharply,
particularly after the mid-session, and even posted further losses
of the stock market Wednesday following fresh selling by operators
as well as financial institutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
