<HEADLINE> Nepal to Ban Ad on Alcohol, Tobacco in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The cabinet of Nepal has
decided to ban from February 19 the advertisement of alcohol and
tobacco products in the electronic media, a senior official said
here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Information and Communications and Parliamentary
Affairs Jaya Prakash Prasad Gupta told a press conference that the
decision was made taking into account the health of the people.
</P>
<P>
