<HEADLINE> China Imports 56 Airplanes In 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- China Aviation Supplies Import
and Export Corporation records show that China imported 56
aircraft in 1998.
</P>
<P>
They consisted of 25 from Boeing, 16 from Airbus, 7 from
McDonnell-Douglas, 5 MIG-171 helicopters, and 3 from ATR in
France.
</P>
<P>
China's three biggest airlines were the biggest buyers. The
China Eastern Air Group bought four MD-90s and 3 Boeing 737s, Air
China imported 3 Boeing 777s and 2 Boeing 747s, and China
Southern Airlines purchased five Airbus 320s.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang Airlines, in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
was the biggest buyer among regional airlines, with 2 Boeing 757s
and 3 ATRs.
</P>
<P>
Sichuan Airlines purchased one Airbus 321.
</P>
<P>
According to the China Aviation Supplies Import and Export
Corporation, all 56 of the new aircraft are in operation.
</P>
