<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Childhood Asthma Cases rise in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Cases of asthma among children
across Canada jumped dramatically over the last two decades,
according to the latest government data.
</P>
<P>
The Statistics Canada study released Tuesday concludes that
between 1978 and 1995 there was more than a four-fold increase in
childhood asthma cases.
</P>
<P>
According to the research, an estimated 2.5 percent of
children under age 15, or about 141,000, were diagnosed with
asthma in 1978-79. By 1994-95, 11.2 percent of children had
asthma, or about 672,000.
</P>
<P>
Throughout the study period, asthma was more commonly reported
among boys than girls. In 1978-79, 3.4 percent of boys and 1.6
percent of girls had asthma. By 1994-95, 13 percent of boys and 9
percent of girls had it. According to the study, boys are also
more likely to be hospitalized.
</P>
<P>
The data also indicates that children in middle-income
households have a significantly lower incidence of asthma,
compared with those in both lower-and-higher-income households.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990113.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 113 People Die From AIDS in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 13 (Xinhua) -- By the end of last year,
1,189 people in Nepal were afflicted with HIV, the virus which
causes AIDS, and 113 people had died from AIDS, the official RSS
news agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Among them, 650 contracted AIDS through sex, 298 through
prostitution, 150 from syringe use and 87 through blood
transfusion, RSS said, quoting information from the National AIDS
and the Sexually Transmitted Diseases Center.
</P>
<P>
And 690 of them were aged between 20 and 29 and 11 were
children under the age of five, the news agency added.
</P>
<P>
It noted that according to an estimate of the World Health
Organization, 100,000 people in Nepal will be afflicted with HIV
by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Some 300,000 Nepalese women and girls are working in Indian
brothels and half of them are believed to have contracted AIDS, it
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
