<DOCNO> XIE19990113.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Lower Prices Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The retail price index and the
consumer price index in China last year slipped by 2.6 percent
and 0.8 percent, respectively, from 1997, according to the State
Development Planning Commission and the National Statistics B
ureau.
</P>
<P>
Although last December saw a 0.2 percent rise in the retail
price index over November, the figure is still 2.7 percent lower
than that of the same month of 1997.
</P>
<P>
The consumer price index in December edged up 0.2 percent over
the previous month, but still down one percent compared with the
corresponding month in 1997. 
</P>
