<HEADLINE> Villa Manager Gregory Appeals to Hoddle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, January 13 (Xinhua) -- English Premier League club
Aston Villa manager John Gregory is urging Glenn Hoddle to step
in and stop central defender Gareth Barry being chosen for the
World Under-20 Championships.
</P>
<P>
Barry is a near certainty for Football Association technical
director Howard Wilkinson's squad for the three-week tournament
in Nigeria in April.
</P>
<P>
But Gregory believes that rising star Barry, already an
under-21 international, will gain more experience that will stand
him in good stead with England by playing in the Premiership
rather than a youth tournament.
</P>
<P>
Gregory said: "Gareth will be more beneficial to Glenn Hoddle
if he is playing in the Premiership rather than an under-20
tournament in Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
"The next best thing to playing for the England senior team is
to be playing at the game's highest level in this country.
</P>
<P>
"Premiership experience is even more beneficial than playing
for the England under-21 side. I cannot see the reasoning in
Gareth going away for a tournament like this when he can be
involved in Premiership games."
</P>
<P>
Gregory also believes that Villa's involvement in the title
chase should be taken into consideration by Wilkinson when
selecting his squad.
</P>
<P>
Gregory said: "Some players who are called up will be squad
members at their clubs but Gareth is an established first-team
player.
</P>
<P>
"There's every chance he will be called up but I would like to
think I would have the full support of the England manager in
this instance." 
</P>
