town and discussed China's gross-roots elections with people's
deputies of the city of Chongqing, which covers 80,000 sq.km. and
has a population of 30 million. It is the largest industrial and
commercial city in southwestern China and a major economic center
on the upper reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, 20 million people in 1,478
townships under its jurisdiction are qualified to vote.  
