Euro from 0.5552, while the local unit was buying 71.42 Japanese
yen from 71.11 at Tuesday's close.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday night in Brazil, the Central Bank intervened in the
foreign exchange market as large outflows of U.S. currency
pressured the local market.
</P>
<P>
Also the Japanese central bank spent more than 4.45 billion
U.S. dollars to halt the yen's rise against the dollar after the
American currency sank to 108.5 yen.
</P>
<P>
The intervention boosted the U.S. dollar back up to around the
112 yen area.

