<HEADLINE> Chinese Companies To Be Listed On NASDAQ </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Frank Zarb, the president of
the U.S. National Association of Securities Dealers and CEO of
NASDAQ, says that this year the first group of Chinese companies
will be listed on NASDAQ, the second biggest stock market in the
United States and the world's first computerized stock market.
</P>
<P>
Three to six companies will be a good target, he says, and if
they perform well and the results are good, then more will follow.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that Securities Dealers and NASDAQ have had
discussions with the China Securities Regulatory Commission, the
country's securities market watchdog, on personnel exchanges and
professional training and have agreed to launch a joint website
soon.
</P>
<P>
NASDAQ has some 6,000 corporations, including 500 from outside
the U.S. The criterion for listing is simply "high quality," Zarb
said, and that could translate into strong leadership, products
or services with potential profitability, and company integrity.
</P>
