<DOCNO> XIE19990113.0143 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Reports Fewer Fires in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sources from provincial fire-fighting headquarters said there
were a total of 2,908 fires reported there last year, the fewest
number in four years.
</P>
<P>
But officials remain "deeply concerned" because 11 counties
still have no professional fire-fighting brigades, and many
fire-fighting units in the province's cities are not properly
equipped or are still using outdated equipment.
</P>
<P>
Only 55.3 percent of the communities in urban areas have
installed fire hydrants, though 83.5 percent of the buildings do
have fire-extinguishing apparatus ready for use, sources said.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting on fire prevention and fire-fighting held here
today, the provincial leaders called for more effective
implementation of fire-prevention laws and increased efforts to
reduce fires this winter. 
</P>
