<HEADLINE> China Accuses Wei Jingsheng's Taiwan Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- China on Tuesday expressed
displeasure at Wei Jingsheng's recent Taiwan tour and pointed out
that Wei's allegations made during his stay in the island was
intended to prevent reunification across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who is on medical parole in the United States, paid a
two-week visit to Taiwan as a "visiting scholar" last month.
</P>
<P>
During Wei's stay in Taiwan, he met with several high-ranking
officials of the Taiwan authorities and discussed so-called
"political cooperation."
</P>
<P>
"The Taiwan authorities gave him a good opportunity and he
responded in kind" by attacking the reunification policies of the
Chinese mainland.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of Taiwan authorities sang the same tune as Wei
against the Chinese mainland, asserting that their cooperation
was for the purpose of making use of each other.
</P>
<P>
In concluding his Taiwan visit, Wei called his meeting with
leaders of the Taiwan authorities a new phase of the relations
between the "democratic movement" and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
In return, the Taiwan authorities denied a national basis for
cross-straits reunification and repeated that "the democratic
movement is an important precondition and target of cross-straits
reunification," and "the two sides of the Taiwan Straits can be
reunified only when the mainland is democratized."
</P>
<P>
Although the Taiwan authorities treated Wei as a distinguished
guest, the Taiwan media had a cold response to his behavior.
</P>
<P>
Critics say that invitations from the Taiwan authorities
extended to the Dalai Lama and Wei Jingsheng are an obvious
expression of its confrontation with the mainland, and this will
surely hurt the people in Taiwan and the cross-straits relations
if this policy of confrontation continues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
