<HEADLINE> Li Peng Solicits Public Opinion on Contract Law (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, visited a
Beijing district court today to solicit opinions concerning
formulation of the country's first unified Contract Law.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday some 30 government officials, legal and economic
experts, industry leaders, judges at various levels and attorneys
expressed their opinions during a seminar held in the Great Hall
of the People and a second seminar held today at the Fengtai
District Court in southwest Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The new law will integrate the three sometimes contradictory
laws on economic, foreign trade and technology contracts.
</P>
<P>
The new law will serve as the foundation for the market
economy. Various stipulations and major principles in the law
have attracted attention nationwide.
</P>
<P>
Reports indicate that 3,000-odd deputies will deliberate the
important draft law during the full NPC session in March.
</P>
<P>
Li said the contract legislation should proceed in conjunction
with the pace of reform and opening. He said the law should
incorporate international conventions and standard practices to
promote the continued development of foreign trade.
</P>
</TEXT>
