<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Opens Three Immigration Offices Along </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has decided to
open immigration offices in three border towns of Dobil Weyni,
Togo Wuchale and Teferi Ber along the Ethio-Somali border to check
foreigners entering or leaving the country illegally through the
Somali State, "the Ethiopian Herald" reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Muhe Dinebsen, head of the Jijiga office
immigration and nationality affairs main department as saying that
a total of 50 persons -- Ethiopians, Somalis, Yemenites and other
citizens -- are leaving or entering Ethiopia daily through Somali
State due to the absence of such offices other than the one in
Jijiga.
</P>
<P>
The report said, most of these are either merchants or tourists
entering the country without legal documents.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government has allocated funds for the opening of
 the three new immigration office, the report added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
