<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopians to Be Repatriated From Netherlands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Some 924 Ethiopian refugees
in the Netherlands will be voluntarily repatriated to their home
land within the next few months, the local English weekly "The
reporter" reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopians are coming under a new Dutch governmental
program that will repatriate and rehabilitate Ethiopians who wish
to return to their country.
</P>
<P>
According to the newspaper, the Consul General of Ethiopia to
the Netherlands, Abdulkadir Risku, has confirmed the report but
did not authenticate the figures.
</P>
<P>
Abdulkadir was quoted by the newspaper as saying that Ethiopia
will be the first country to benefit from this scheme.
</P>
<P>
He said, the Dutch government has opened an office in Addis
Ababa to repatriate illegal immigrants and to rehabilitate them
through aid.
</P>
<P>
The refugees will be returned "voluntarily and with dignity",
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
