<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Opposition Tables No-Confidence Motion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Thai opposition parties
submitted a no-confidence motion against three key members of the
cabinet to House Speaker Wan Muhammad Nor Matha on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The motion was proposed by the opposition leader, New
Aspiration Party Leader Chavalit Yongchaiyudh and Prachakorn Thai
Party Leader Samak Sundaravej.
</P>
<P>
They charged the three key ministers, Deputy Prime Minister and
Interior Minister Sanan Kachornprasart, Finance Minister Tarrin
Nimmanhaeminda and Transport and Communication Minister Suthep
Thueksuban, of corruption, malfeasance and mismanagement.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the opposition claimed that it has substantial
incriminating evidence against the three ministers, all from the
Democrat Party, the core party of the ruling coalition.
</P>
<P>
The opposition has said that it is unlikely to win the censure
debate, but it is hoping that by grilling the three ministers, the
image and reputation of the Chuan Leekpai government could be
damaged.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that the parliament will hold a two-day censure
debate, the second of its kind since Chuan took his office in
November 1997, at the end of this month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
