<HEADLINE> Chang Advances at Kooyong Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Michael Chang of the United
States fought back from one set down to overcome Russian Yevgeny
Kafelnikov 6-7 (5-7), 6-3, 7-5 at the Kooyong Classic exhibition
event to warm up perfectly for next week's Australian Open.
</P>
<P>
Sweden's Thomas Enqvist edged Croatia's Goran Ivanisevic 7-6
(7-4), 7-6 (7-5), while Australian Mark Philippoussis came from a
set down to beat Englishman Tim Henman 2-6, 6-4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
In an early match today, world number six Andre Agassi crushed
the drug-embroiled Petr Korda 6-2, 6-1.
</P>
<P>
Korda, facing a compulsory Association of Tennis Professional
(ATP) meeting on Saturday to thrash out his lenient punishment
after failing a drug test, was obviously out of form and fell
down after just 56 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Korda tested positive for steroids at last year's Wimbledon
but International Tennis Federation (ITF) fell short of banning
him after accepting his claim that he took the drug unknowingly.
</P>
