<HEADLINE> Philippine Gov't Probes Group Raid on Drug Pushers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government
Wednesday launched an investigation into reports that the Moro
Islamic Liberation Front (MILF) rounded up 42 suspected drug
pushers during a raid last Tuesday in Marawi City in Mindanao, the
southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the Department of Interior and Local Governments
said the investigators would look into the real motive behind the
raid.
</P>
<P>
The MILF has no right to conduct the raid even if its purpose
was to round up suspected drug pushers, they said.
</P>
<P>
At least 50 MILF members reportedly raided a public market in
Marawi City, rounding up suspected drug pushers who, they said,
would be publicly executed.
</P>
<P>
The officials said that Philippine President Joseph Estrada is
set to sign an executive order creating a powerful central agency
to coordinate his administration's anti-drug efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
