<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong Province Stimulating Domestic Demand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 13 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province
expects to take effective measures this year to increase demand
locally in an effort to give impetus to local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The province will focus on the regulation and direction of con
sumer price systems in the areas of real estate,
telecommunications, automobiles and power.
</P>
<P>
Efforts will be made to standardize local land-transfer prices
and further improve the system of compensation for those who must
move out of old buildings scheduled for demolition. Prices for
commodities, especially affordable housing, will be practically
reduced.
</P>
<P>
Shandong will also reduce telecommunications fees including
those for telephone installation, mobile phones and long-distance
telephone calls.
</P>
<P>
Automobile prices and charges for follow-up services will be
lower in the province, and procedures will be simplified to
encourage private car purchases in the province.
</P>
<P>
The price of electricity will also be reduced for local
customers.
</P>
<P>
As a result of all these measures, consumer prices for local
citizens are expected to grow by only five percent this year, and
commodity retail-sale prices by only three percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
