<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S.Lankan Govt. Troops Kill 9 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka government troops
confronted the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) rebels
Tuesday in separate clashes in the north and east of the country,
killing nine rebels, a military spokesman said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops on patrol northeast
of Nedunkerni confronted a group of terrorists, killing three
rebels.
</P>
<P>
In another incident at northwest of Oddusudan, government
troops operating forward of defenses sniped and killed two Tamil
rebels, said Dewage, adding that government troops conducted a
small group operation north of Oddusudan and killed three rebels.
</P>
<P>
Around 12:15 p.m. at Ponnankanittoddam in the Batticaloa
district, government troops in ambush confronted a group of rebels
and killed one, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a war against the government
for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country
since 1983. So far nearly 60,000 people are reported to have been
killed in the war. 
</P>
</TEXT>
