<HEADLINE> Hubei Province to Host Ski Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hubei Province
is set to host a month-long ski festival as part of the
nationwide eco-tourism campaign.
</P>
<P>
The Shennongjia Forestry Resort, the southernmost venue of its
kind in China, will host the event beginning on January 30.
</P>
<P>
The resort will offer training for beginners, as well as a
speedskating competition and popular ski events such as slalom
races.
</P>
<P>
Shennongjia has completed a number of facilities, including a
ski tow and new hotels. Reports indicate that the resort has
received over 30 centimeters of fresh snow in recent days, with
temperatures on the slopes averaging at eight degrees below zero
centigrade.
</P>
<P>
The Hubei Tourism Bureau and the resort will jointly sponsor
the festival. 
</P>
