<HEADLINE> Philippines Halts Land Conversion Requests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government will
stop accepting land conversion applications and wait until new
land conversion regulations for promoting farm development and
food security are issued.
</P>
<P>
Agrarian Reform Secretary Horacio Morales said Wednesday that
the suspension will give his department ample time to review the
present policy on land conversion.
</P>
<P>
He also clarified that all applications for land conversion
submitted before January 12 will be processed.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Philippine President Joseph Estrada has ordered the
Department of Agrarian Reform to release not later than March 30
the revised rules and regulations on land conversion.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said the revised regulations should be in consonance
with the principles of sound agricultural development and food
security, and the sustainable use of land resources and protection
of the tenurial status of small farmers and occupants. 
</P>
