<HEADLINE> Chinese Media Focus on Macao Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- As the handover of Macao is
now less than a year away, the Chinese media are focusing on this
earliest colony, which will be returned to China this year on
December 20.
</P>
<P>
Two major Chinese broadcasting stations have already presented
a series of programs on Macao. Central People's Broadcasting
Station's new 78-episode radio program has been aired, and a
10-episode documentary entitled Days in Macao was recently
released on China Central Television during prime time.
</P>
<P>
Both programs offered audiences a comprehensive picture of
Macao with political, economic, and cultural perspectives,
especially emphasizing the various views of the people of Macao
on the future of their land.
</P>
<P>
Macao is also making headlines in The People's Daily and other
local newspapers, and reporters from 20 major Beijing-based media
organizations have formed a news group for on-the-spot coverage
of Macao. 
</P>
