<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Joseph
Estrada has offered a reward of 2.5 million U.S. dollars to the
country's highest food-producing province by yearend as an
incentive for pursuing food security.
</P>
<P>
The second-highest food-producing province will get 1.5 million
U.S. dollars, with the third to receive 1 million U.S dollars,
Estrada said at a gathering of governors Tuesday night.
