<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Have One More University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Sri Lankan government has
approved the establishment of a university in the North Western
province, government sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The North Western province is a crucial location where the
provincial council election is being bitterly and violently fought
with voting due on January 25.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the government has announced the proposal to set
up this university at Kuliyapitiya on a 47-acre land with hostel
facilities for 400 students, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said while the preliminary expenditure will be
borne by the University Grants Commission, the government proposes
allocating a sum of 100 million rupees (1.5 million U.S. dollars)
for infrastructure development.
</P>
<P>
At present there are 12 universities in Sri Lanka in different
provinces but there is no university in the North Western
province. 
