<HEADLINE> Roundup: Bangkok Haunted by Spate of Bomb Hoaxes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A series of bomb hoaxes have
haunted Bangkok and put police on high alert, police sources said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Several rank calls had been made to the 191 police radio center
 Tuesday alone about possible bomb attacks at various spots in
Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The International School of Bangkok was closed Wednesday after
receiving a bomb threat the day before.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday night, the school said the campus had closed at 6 p.m.
local time for "security reasons". Police sent officers and
sniffer dogs to the scene but found nothing.
</P>
<P>
In a related development, police arrested a woman Tuesday on
suspicion of making a hoax call about a bomb at a restraurant in
downtown Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
The woman, Sukanya Chanthong, made the call to the 191 police
radio center on a cellular phone at 11 p.m. local time Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sukanya, 20, admitted she had made the hoax call for fun and
expressed regret for her action.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the U.S. Embassy in Bangkok also received a bomb
threat and was closed for one day.
</P>
<P>
Recently a spate of bombings have rocked the city but caused no
casualties. Police are still searching for the suspects. The
motive of the bombings remains unknown.
</P>
<P>
The bombings have prompted the government to step up security
at official buildings and public places.
</P>
<P>
In a latest bomb attack Monday night, the house of a former
official of the Muang district municipality was damaged.
</P>
<P>
The explosion caused the office roof to cave in and shattered
the windows, but no one was injured.
</P>
<P>
Bomb experts suspected the attack to be the work of a
professional. The bomb was a home-made device using materials
similar to those used in quarries and was only meant to
intimidate, police said.
</P>
<P>
The targeted house is close to the Democrat Party headquarters
and police are investigating whether the blast is in any way
connected to a series of recent bombings in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
