<DOCNO> XIE19990113.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai Government Intervenes Rubber Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Thai government has resumed
its intervention to curb the drop of rubber prices, government
sources said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Since this week, the government has spent 10.1 million baht
(280,555 U.S. dollars) to buy 470,000 tons of rubber.
</P>
<P>
A total of 4 billion baht (1.1 billion dollars) has been set
aside for the intervention, according to Deputy Agriculture
Minister Newin Chidchob.
</P>
<P>
Newin said earlier that the intervention project had so far
drawn "unsatisfactory" response due to some criteria used, weak
public relations and a limited number of buying points.
</P>
<P>
Agencies concerned are to meet later Wednesday to consider
allowing planters to sell more rubber daily and the opening of
more buying points.
</P>
<P>
Rubber planters are currently allowed to sell based on the
ratio of two kilos per rai (one rai equals 0.16 hectares) per day.
They might be allowed to sell more, probably at three kilos per
rai per day, Newin said.
</P>
<P>
Newin claimed the price intervention had helped convince
traders to buy rubber at the prices close to those offered by the
government -- 21.65 baht (60 U.S. cents) per kilo for first grade
rubber, 21.35 baht (59 cents) per kilo for second grade rubber ,
21 baht (58 cents) for third grade rubber and 20 baht (55 cents)
for fourth grade rubber.
</P>
<P>
Newin said he believed that rubber prices would "certainly" go
up but could not say by how much.
</P>
<P>
He said private warehouses paid by the Office of the Rubber
Replanting Aid Fund to keep rubber at the rate of 85 bath (2.36
dollars) per ton/month would have to pay for damage caused to the
rubber in their storage.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Prasit Damrongchai, permanent secretary of the Prime
Minister's Office, said a working group had been set up to monitor
the use of the 4-billion-baht fund for the price intervention
scheme. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
