<HEADLINE> Nepal Against Adoption of Children by Foreigners </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Nepali government would
halt any initiative for adoption of Nepali children by foreigners,
The Kathmandu Post Wednesday quoted a senior official as saying.
</P>
<P>
"It is inappropriate to abandon your children in favor of
foreigners, an act comparable to selling," Home Minister Govind
Raj Joshi Tuesday told a symposium on the existing laws on
adoption.
</P>
<P>
"Why don't we abandon our own children if adoption by
foreigners is so good?" he further said. His ministry decides on
applications for adoption.
</P>
<P>
The Country Code has allowed adoption of Nepali children by
foreigners in the past two decades.
</P>
<P>
By mid-November 1998, a total of 788 children had been adopted
by foreigners, most of them Europeans and Americans, The Kathmandu
Post said.
</P>
<P>
The daily said that 150 foreigners are awaiting decision on
their applications for adoption of Nepali children.
</P>
<P>
Adoption by foreigners is criticized in Nepal on grounds of
national dignity and ethics, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
