<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stimulant Drug Tablets Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 13 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
398,000 stimulant tablets in the country's eastern Shan state
early this month, the official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was made by a combined team of regional
intelligence unit and police who raided a house in Tachilek on
January 3, uncovering also machinery and utensils and chemicals
used in making the stimulant drugs.
</P>
<P>
The local police station has taken action against two people in
connection with the case under Myanmar's Narcotic Drugs and
Psychotropic Substances Law, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, the Myanmar authorities
confiscated over 11 million stimulant drug tablets in the first
nine months of last year.
</P>
<P>
Other statistics also show that during the first six months of
last year, Myanmar seized a total of 4,927 kilograms of narcotics
including 219 kg of heroin and 4,471 kg of opium, destroyed 15
heroin refineries and 8,000 hectares of poppy plantations.
</P>
</TEXT>
