<DOCNO> XIE19990113.0298 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-01-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Machine-Building Industry To Concentrate on Rural Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- China's machine-building
industry has to improve its production capacity and marketing in
order to tap into the big potential market in rural areas, the
State Administration of Machinery Industry SAMI) director Shao
Qihui warned recently.
</P>
<P>
He announced that in the next five years, the industry will
concentrate on developing technology and products that meet the
demand in rural areas.
</P>
<P>
"The auto industry has failed to capture the market for
vehicles in rural areas due to a lack of market research. This is
a profound lesson that the whole machine-building industry should
learn," said Zhang Xiaoyu, deputy-director of the SAMI.
</P>
<P>
The annual production output of powered vehicles, including
tractors, for farming areas has now reached 1.8 million units,
far exceeding China's general auto output.
</P>
<P>
But Zhang pointed out that in the past the machinery industry
did not pay enough attention to the rural market and instead
dumped, stockpiled or even sold inferior products in those
areas.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics supplied by SAMI, farming communities
in China will have a need for 3,000 to 5,000 large tractors every
year by 2000. However, at present there is only an annual
production capacity of several hundred large tractors and the
sector has been forced to rely on importing several thousand
tractors annually over the last few years.
</P>
<P>
Yet, there are twelve tractor manufacturers in China with a
total production capability of 100,000 small to medium sized
tractors every year but half of their capacity is idle.
</P>
<P>
At present, only four percent of rice and less than one
percent of corn is mechanically harvested in China but it is
estimated that by 2000, the number of combined harvesters
bringing in the rice crop will increase by 8 to 16 times from
26,000 unit to 50,000. The number for harvesting corn is expected
to increase five fold to 16,000 units.
</P>
<P>
It is also predicted that China will need 2,000 to 3,000 grain
dyers and 60,000 to 70,000 sets of irrigation and water conservan
cy equipment. In addition there will be a huge demand for
cultivating machines, environmental protection and pest control
machines, feed processing machines and diesel engines for farm
machines.
</P>
<P>
The SAMI has listed nine machinery products that it plans to
develop for rural consumers. In the meantime, it recommends the
phasing out of a number of farm machines that have become
obsolete and of no further use on farms.
</P>
<P>
The China National Harvester Machinery Corporation started
manufacturing combined harvesters for bringing in the wheat crop
for individual farmers ten years ago. Now it has become the
largest combined harvester manufacturer in the world, holding
over 70 percent of the Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Company President Lang Zhongqiang said that the company has
become the most profitable enterprise in the country's farm
machine industry because it provides rural consumers with
reliable products and a complete range of after-care services.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
