<HEADLINE> New Regulation Spurs Development of Traditional Medicines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- A newly-adopted regulation
encouraging investment from pharmaceutical or other sectors is
expected to spur development of new traditional Chinese medicines
(TCM).
</P>
<P>
Under the regulation published by the State Administration of
TCM (SATCM), a list of key projects for TCM scientific and
technological research will be published. Research institutes and
investors could participate in open biddings and sign cooperative
contracts.
</P>
<P>
SATCM will supervise contracts and help promote outstanding
research results and products, said today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The administration plans to promulgate another regulation to
tighten management over laboratories for TCM scientific and
technological research programs, it said.
</P>
<P>
The drive will speed up advancement of TCM science and
technology and deliver research results quickly for production
purposes.
</P>
<P>
Currently, only 10 to 20 percent of scientific research
regarding TCMs can be put into production, according to
statistics of SATCM. 
</P>
