<HEADLINE> Israel Backs Thai Official for WTO Top Position </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Israel has voiced its support
for Thai Deputy Prime Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi to bid for
the top position of the World Trade Organization (WTO), the
Bangkok Post reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision was conveyed to the Thai Embassy in Tel Aviv
Monday by the Israeli Foreign Ministry's director for economic
division, Zvi Tenney.
</P>
<P>
