the United Nations in Geneva to inform its Thai counterpart there.
Israeli Ambassador to Thailand David Matnai also met Thai Foreign
Minister Surin Pitsuwan Monday to inform him of the decision.
</P>
<P>
Israel is the 46th country to support Supachai, also commerce
minister and one of the four major contenders to vie for the post
of WTO secretary-general.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Thai embassies in Hungary and South Korea have
received confirmation from the two countries that they will stand
by their earlier pledge to support Supachai. 
</P>
