<HEADLINE> China Develops Super Server System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists claim that
they have developed an advanced computer super server system
which can be widely used in research fields of oil, power, space,
banking and other basic projects.
</P>
<P>
Scientists from National Intelligence Computer Research Center
said the Shuguang 2000-I super server, a major state approved
high-tech project, has been given the green light by experts.
</P>
<P>
They announced that the super server is not only good at
large-scale scientific engineering arithmetic operations, with
the highest floating-point operation speed rated at 20 billion
times per second, but can also deal with problems in the
information, networking and policy-making support fields.
</P>
<P>
Today's People's Daily described the server as of advanced
world level in operational computer group systems, integrated
concurrent program-making environments and server software
accumulation.
</P>
<P>
Chinese experts say that a high-performance computer sector
reflects the scientific abilities of a country. 
</P>
