<HEADLINE> China Calls for Creation of New Security Concept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Chinese delegates attending the
seventh annual meeting of the Asia-Pacific Parliamentary Forum
recommended on Tuesday the creation of a new security concept in
the region.
</P>
<P>
Chinese delegation head Xu Dunxin said the new concept was
necessary for a lasting peace and development in the Asia-Pacific
region.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese legislator said that relations between states
should develop on the basis of peaceful coexistence, mutual
respect for sovereignty and territorial integrity, and
non-intervention in internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Xu, a member of the standing committee of the Chinese National
People's Congress, said that economic development and cooperation
and common prosperity are the economic basis of security in the
region.
</P>
<P>
He said that mutual understanding and trust through dialogue
and cooperation and peaceful solutions to differences and
disputes between states are a feasible means to guarantee
regional safety.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that the East Asia financial crisis shows that
economic security is part of regional safety.
</P>
<P>
He said China has adopted a responsible attitude to curb the
effects of the crisis and the tension in Southern Asia. 
</P>
