<HEADLINE> Brazil's Dunga Goes Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's former World
Cup captain Dunga Tuesday returned to the club where he started
his soccer career.
</P>
<P>
The 35-year-old midfielder signed with Internacional, a club
in the southern Brazil he left more than a decade ago, after
ending a five-year stint with Japan's Jubilo Iwata in December.
</P>
<P>
Dunga captained Brazil at the last two World Cups and retired
from international football after the 3-0 defeat by France in the
1998 final last July.
</P>
<P>
He won 91 caps and scored six goals. 
</P>
