<HEADLINE> UK Backs Romanian Bid to Join NATO: UK Defense Secretary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, January 12 (Xinhua) -- The British government will
fully support Romania's bid to join the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO), visiting British Defense Secretary George
Robertson said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The British government was satisfied with the Romanian
government's achievements in military reform, Robertson said
after talks with his Romanian counterpart Victor Babiuc.
</P>
<P>
The British government values cooperative relations in all
fields with Romania and would like to help Romania's military
forces to modernize, he said.
</P>
<P>
London expected Romania also to play an important role in
peace-keeping in Balkan region, Robertson said.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that NATO had not yet made any decision on the
second round of eastward expansion, and probably would not before
NATO's April summit in Washington.
</P>
<P>
Romanian President Emil Constantinescu, Prime Minister Radu
Vasile and Foreign Minister Andrei Gabriel Plesu also met with
Robertson Tuesday and exchanged views on the eastward expansion
of NATO and the situation in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
Romanian leaders reaffirmed that membership of NATO and the
European Union is the main goal of Romanian foreign policy.
</P>
