<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment in Slovakia Up to 15.4 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Slovakia's unemployment rose to
15.4 percent in 1998, an increase of 2.44 percent on the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures released on Tuesday, a total of
383,000 people registered as the jobless by the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
Unemployment in 1998 was the highest since the republic's
independence in 1993, the figures show.
</P>
<P>
They also show that the unemployment rate was higher than that
of other Eastern European countries such as the Czech Republic,
Poland and Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Economists attributed the increase to unreasonable economic
structure and poor management and called for reforms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
