<HEADLINE> Herminator Wins Giant Slalom Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Overall World Cup leader
Hermann Maier of Austria took the men's giant slalom title in
Adelboden, Switzerland on Tuesday, clocking a time of two minutes
and 16.66 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian double Olympic gold medallist, claimed his sixth
win of the season and the 17th of his career, by defeating
Norway's Andre Kjetil Aamodt by 0.28 seconds with Austrian
Benjamin Raich, who was fastest on the first run, came third 0.82
seconds back.
</P>
<P>
The win extended the 26-year-old Maier's lead in the overall
standings and reduced the lead of Switzerland's Michael von
Grunigen, who finished sixth, to just two points in the giant
slalom standings. 
