<HEADLINE> Top UEFA officials condemn Blatter's World Cup plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 12 (Xinhua) -- Senior UEFA officials rejected
FIFA president Sepp Blatter's plan to hold the World Cup every
two years here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued after a meeting of the five-member
presidential board, UEFA said it was rejecting Blatter's proposal
on sporting, medical and commercial grounds.
</P>
<P>
It said that the Presidential Board not only objected to the
idea but also condemned the way the project was presented,
without prior consultation with any of the relevant bodies.
</P>
<P>
The Board believes that the project would produce negative
consequences in sporting, medical and commercial contexts and
have a damaging effect on domestic competitions, it said in the
statement.
</P>
<P>
The Board, composed of UEFA president Lennart Johansson and
four UEFA vice-presidents, also questioned Blatter's motives by
saying "the project could be a matter of personal prestige".
</P>
<P>
Blatter first made public his wish to introduce a biennial
World Cup in an interview with a Swiss newspaper at the beginning
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Johansson has already voiced publicly his personal negative
opinions about the plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
