<HEADLINE> Oversupply of College Graduates in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 13 (Xinhua) -- With the reduction of
government departments and the cutting down on staff in
institutions and enterprises, college graduates will find it hard
to find a job in Beijing this year, according to the Beijing
Educational Commission.
</P>
<P>
Figures released today show that more than 60,000 college
students and post-graduates will graduate from 65 colleges and
universities and 110 research institutions in Beijing this year,
the largest number in history.
</P>
<P>
Graduates majoring in basic theories, foreign trade, geology,
philosophy, history and management are apparently in oversupply.
</P>
<P>
But students majoring in computer, telecommunications,
electronics, finance, teaching, English and clinical medicine are
still in great demand, so are students from elite universities
such as Qinghua University. 
</P>
</TEXT>
