back of a weak Wall Street opening amid a lack of fresh corporate
news with the leading Dax index closed down 70 points at 5200.1.
</P>
<P>
Traders forecast that the market will remain in consolidating
mode for the rest of the week, with the key index hovering around
5200 and 5300 points.
</P>
<P>
The French stock market pulled back in late trade as the Dow's
losses provided an extra excuse to book profits.
</P>
<P>
The leading Cac 40 index finished down 101 points at 4100.3.
One trade said: "It's nothing to worry about, just a little
consolidation after yesterday's rise." 
